1ï¸âƒ£ RDS Deployment

Engine: MySQL

Instance class: db.t3.micro (lab configuration)

Storage: General Purpose (gp2/gp3)

Database identifier: simulearn-db

Public access: Disabled

VPC: Lab VPC

Subnet group: Private subnets

Outcome:
RDS instance successfully provisioned and available.

2ï¸âƒ£ Security Configuration

To allow communication from the Web Server:

Security Group Modified:
DbServerSecurityGroup

Inbound Rule Added:

Type: MySQL/Aurora

Protocol: TCP

Port: 3306

Source: WebServerSecurityGroup

Why this approach:

Follows Principle of Least Privilege

Restricts access to only the application layer

Avoids exposing database to public internet

Uses Security Group referencing instead of CIDR

Because Security Groups are stateful:
Return traffic is automatically allowed.

3ï¸âƒ£ Read Replica Setup

Read Replica was created to:

Improve read scalability

Reduce load on primary instance

Simulate production-grade scaling pattern

Key Observations:

Replica receives asynchronous replication

Used for read-only workloads

Not a backup solution

Does not automatically fail over (unless promoted)

